16 also authorizes a civil action to be brought against a landlord that violates the
17 provisions of section 1 by a person aggrieved by the violation or a district attorney.
THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. Chapter 118A of NRS is hereby amended by
2 adding thereto a new section to read as follows:
3 1. A landlord of a covered premises shall establish:
4 (a) A policy requiring an applicant for employment with the
5 landlord to undergo a criminal background check as a condition
6 of employment if the position for which the applicant is applying
7 entails access to any dwelling unit key; and
8 (b) Written policies and procedures regarding the:
9 (1) Storage, issuance, return and security of dwelling unit
10 keys; and
11 (2) If applicable, the usage and deactivation of dwelling
12 unit keys.
13 2. A landlord of a covered premises shall maintain on the
14 premises a log that accounts for the issuance and return of each
15 dwelling unit key and the written policies and procedures
16 established pursuant to paragraph (b) of subsection 1.
17 3. In addition to any other remedies, if a landlord of a
18 covered premises violates this section, a person aggrieved by the
19 violation or a district attorney may bring a civil action in a court
20 of competent jurisdiction against the landlord to seek any or all of
21 the following relief:
22 (a) Declaratory and injunctive relief.
23 (b) Actual damages.
24 (c) Reasonable attorney’s fees and costs.
25 (d) Any other legal or equitable relief that the court deems
26 appropriate.
27 4. As used in this section:
28 (a) “Covered premises” means:
29 (1) In a county whose population is 100,000 or more, a
30 premises comprising more than 50 dwelling units attached to a
31 single parcel of property; or
32 (2) In a county whose population is less than 100,000, a
33 premises comprising more than 30 dwelling units attached to a
34 single parcel of property.
