1 (b) “Dwelling unit key” means any physical or electronic
2 mechanism used to gain access to a dwelling unit, including,
3 without limitation, a combination or access code.
4 (c) “Financial institution” means any bank, savings and loan
5 association, savings bank, thrift company, credit union or
6 financial institution that is licensed, registered or otherwise
7 authorized to do business in this State.
8 (d) “Landlord” does not include a financial institution, real
9 estate broker, real estate broker-salesperson or real estate
10 salesperson.
11 (e) “Real estate broker” has the meaning ascribed to it in
12 NRS 645.030.
13 (f) “Real estate broker-salesperson” has the meaning ascribed
